        <p>I’ve always had a passion for science and as a child, remember this being my favorite subject in school. As a result, I pursued a Ph.D. in cell biology and completed a post-doctoral fellowship in cancer biology. Cancer research, specifically breast cancer, is my passion and now that I’m an assistant professor at an osteopathic medical school, I have established a lab which aims to better understand how the cells and non-cellular material which surround the breast cancer cells influence breast tumor growth. I love what I do and blessed to be able to call my work a hobby. I look forward to discovering something new every day and it is with hope that these discoveries will someday benefit the millions of individuals suffering from cancer.</p>
